[[File:Kubuli Beer Bottle.jpg|right|thumb|Kubuli Beer Bottle]] '''Kubuli''' is a golden [[lager]] brewed in [[Dominica]], where it is the unofficial national [[beer]]. The beer's name is derived from the [[Island Caribs]] name for the island, ''Wai‘tu kubuli'', which means "Tall is her body."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dominica.dm/site/dominica.cfm |title=Discover Dominica: an introduction to our Caribbean island |publisher=Dominica.dm |date= |accessdate=2018-07-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100923082054/http://dominica.dm/site/dominica.cfm |archivedate=23 September 2010 |df=dmy }}</ref> The water used to make Kubuli comes from Dominica's own Loubière Springs.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uncommoncaribbean.com/2011/06/17/friday-happy-hour-kubuli-beer-the-pride-of-dominica/ |title=Friday Happy Hour: Kubuli, The Pride of Dominica|publisher=Uncommon Caribbean|last=Bennett|first=Steve|date=23 July 2012 |accessdate=2017-04-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170405172908/https://www.uncommoncaribbean.com/2011/06/17/friday-happy-hour-kubuli-beer-the-pride-of-dominica/ |archivedate=2017-04-05 |df= }} </ref> The beer is the flagship product of Dominica Brewery Limited, a subsidiary of [[Cervecería Nacional Dominicana]] (itself a subsidiary of [[AmBev]], which in turn is a subsidiary of [[Anheuser-Busch InBev]]) as of February 24, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapid=30661797 |title=Dominica Brewery & Beverages Ltd.: Private Company Information |publisher=[[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]] |date=2010-02-24 |accessdate=2017-07-07}}</ref><ref name=cnd>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnd.com.do/index.php/exportaciones/cerveceras-en-el-caribe/dominica-brewery-limited|language=es|accessdate=24 July 2018|title=Dominica Brewery Limited|publisher=Cervecería Nacional Dominicana}}</ref> As of 2018, the brand held a 68% market share of the local beer market.<ref name=cnd/> Dominica Brewery exports the beer across the [[Caribbean]], to such places as [[Saint Lucia]], [[Saint Kitts]], [[Barbados]], [[Guadeloupe]], [[Martinique]], [[Montserrat]], [[Antigua and Barbuda]], [[Anguilla]], and the [[British Virgin Islands|British]] and [[United States Virgin Islands|U.S. Virgin Islands]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://dominicanewsonline.com/news/homepage/news/business/kubuli-beer-hits-st-lucian-market/ |title=Kubuli Beer hits St. Lucian market – Dominica News Online |website=Dominicanewsonline.com |date= |accessdate=2017-07-07}}</ref>
